From: AgenticBrowser <build@agentic-browser.dev>
Subject: [PATCH] Pin HTTP/3 QUIC transport parameters to Chrome's values

Detection vector: QUIC fingerprinting reads the transport parameters
in the TLS handshake (initial_max_data, max_idle_timeout, etc.) and
the QUIC version negotiation. Non-Chrome clients produce different
parameter sets.

This patch ensures the QUIC client sends Chrome 138's exact transport
parameters.

Surface: network-h3
Closes: QUIC/HTTP3 transport fingerprinting

--- a/net/quic/quic_context.cc
+++ b/net/quic/quic_context.cc
@@ -XX,7 +XX,7 @@ void QuicContext::Initialize() {
+  // AgenticBrowser: pin QUIC transport parameters to Chrome 138 values.
+  params->initial_max_data = 1048576;
+  params->initial_max_stream_data_bidi_local = 65536;
+  params->initial_max_stream_data_bidi_remote = 65536;
+  params->initial_max_stream_data_uni = 65536;
+  params->initial_max_streams_bidi = 100;
+  params->initial_max_streams_uni = 100;
+  params->max_idle_timeout = quic::QuicTime::Delta::FromSeconds(30);
+  params->max_udp_payload_size = 1350;
